An archbishop in Uganda has cautioned both citizens and security agents against provoking one another, saying it is costing lives besides creating more disunity in the country ahead of the forthcoming elections.
“Don’t provoke one another, whether those of other parties or security. Let us promote peace and harmony in our country,” Gulu Archbishop John Baptist Odama said to his congregation on New Year’s day at St Joseph’s Cathedral in Gulu City.



