The archbishop said provocation has resulted in the loss of lives, which is uncalled for.
“We must put it into our hearts and minds that the care of one another as Ugandans must take priority, no matter the positions you have or jobs or political parties and religious groups you belong to. Let us start the year together up to the end…,” Archbishop Odama said.



